/PG770/XX/PR
/KASinai/XX/PR
The men rushed ahead/PR
They always do/PR
in battle, to defend us/PR
in eagerness, to get the best view/PR
to be there with each other/PR
as a community/PR
/PR
We followed later/PR
some of us waited/PR
till we were done nursing/PR
others waited to go together/PR
with those who were still nursing/PR
most of us were herding several children/PR
carrying a heavy two year old/PR
On one hip/PR
(itÚs hard to move forward quickly/PR
with a heavy two year old on one hip)/PR
last came the very pregnant ones/PR
when youÚre that far along/PR
itÚs your instinct to be afraid of crowds/PR
afraid of being jostled/PR
you hang back/PR
you feel safer being last/PR
/PR
Anyway, I was one of the ones/PR
with a heavy two year old on one hip/PR
such a sweet body he had/PR
warm soft delicious flesh/PR
he was afraid of the noise/PR
he clung to me so tightly/PR
his fingers in my neck/PR
his face buried in my neck/PI/PR
/PR
/PR
/PR
/PL771/XX/PR
I showered him with little kisses/PR
not so much to comfort him/PR
as out of habit/PR
and my pleasure/PR
/PR
The earth shook, it vibrated/PR
and so did I/PR
my chest, my legs/PR
all vibrating/PR
I sank to my knees/PR
all the while with this little boy attached to me/PR
trying to merge himself back into me/PR
/PR
I closed my eyes/PR
to be there more intensely/PR
it all washed over me/PR
wave upon wave upon wave.../PR
/PR
And afterwards, the stillness/PR
of a nation, a people/PR
who had been flattened/PR
forever imprinted/PR
slowly raising themselves/PR
rising again from the earth/PR
/PR
How to hold onto that moment/PR
washed clean/PR
reborn/PR
holy silence/PR
Merle Feld/XX/PR
