/PL777/XXREADINGS: PEACE/XX/PR
A peace/PR
without the big noise of beating swords into plowshares,/PR
without words, without/PR
the heavy thud of the rubber stamp; I want it/PR
gentle over us, like lazy white foam./PR
A little rest for the wounds--/PR
who speaks of healing?/PR
(And the orphansÚ outcry is passed from one generation/PR
to the next, as in a relay race:/PR
that baton never falls.)/PR
/PR
I want it to come/PR
like wildflowers,/PR
suddenly, because the field/PR
needs it: wildpeace/PR
Yehuda Amichai (translated by Chana Bloch and Ariel Bloch)/XX/PR
