/KAWe Mothers/XX/PR
We mothers,/PR
we gather seeds of desire/PR
from oceanic night,/PR
we are gatherers/PR
of scattered goods,/PR
/PR
We mothers,/PR
pacing dreamily/PR
with the constellations,/PR
the floods/PR
of past and future,/PR
leave us alone/PR
with our birth/PR
like an island./PR
/PR
We mothers/PR
who say to death:/PR
blossom in our blood,/PR
We who impel sand to love and bring/PR
a mirroring world to the stars--/PR
/PR
We mothers,/PR
who rock in the cradles/PR
the shadowy memories/PR
of creationÚs day--/PR
the to and fro of each breath/PR
is the melody of our love song./PR
/PR
We mothers/PR
rock into the heart of the world/PR
the melody of peace./PR
Nelly Sachs (translated from the German by Ruth and Matthew Mead)/XX/PR
